        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 4:05PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 405 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Needmore, or near Haleyville, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haleyville, Addison, Sardis, Brushy Lake, Moreland, Inmanfield,
Needmore, Posey Field Airport, Upshaw, Pebble, Sipsey River Rec Area,
Grayson, Addison Municipal Airport, and Bankhead National Forest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
